The paper proposes a method for compressing neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically falls under the category of model compression. The use of tensor decomposition and Bayesian methods also suggests a focus on optimization and probabilistic modeling, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY. The experiments conducted on fully connected, CNN, and residual neural networks suggest a focus on computer vision, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV. Finally, the use of automatic rank selection suggests a focus on neural network architecture search, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE.
